  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.9688" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>
          <placeName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.290">Rio de Janeiro</placeName>
          <lb/> Feb. 3<hi rendition="#sup">d</hi> 1882.<lb/> Prof. Dr. Hugo Schuchardt:<lb/>
        </dateline>
        <opener>Dear Sir,</opener>
        <p>On receipt of your favor of Dec 20, inquiring about modifications of the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.844">Portuguese language</ref> among the negroes of <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5957">
Brazil</placeName>, I referred it at once to General <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2102">Couto de Magalhães</persName>
          <note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2102">Couto de Magalhães</persName> (1837-1898), brasil. Offizier, Politiker, Ethnologe, Folklorist und Autor; vgl. HSA 
06773 (<bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.1600">Wolf, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Nachlaß</hi>
              </ref>
            </bibl>, 46, gibt den Vornamen irrtümlich mit <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">Conto</hi> an).</note> one of our greatest travelers and our best authority on Indian languages. You will find his reply enclosed.<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">
HSA 
06773, datiert auf den 29.1.1882.</note>
        </p>

        <p>In the absence of any work on the subject I have made inquiry for some romance or similar words in which negro characters are introduced but have so far been unable to learn of anything that would <pb
            facs="#IMG.2"
            n="2"/> serve your purpose. I remember to have seen in the newspapers occasional articles mostly of the nature of <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">skits</hi>
          <note n="3" place="foot"
            type="editorial">Parodie, Sketch.</note> at various individuals in which an attempt was made to imitate negro phraseology. I fancy that this will be of no use to you but when I meet with them again I will send you some as example of how the negroes talk <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.844">Portuguese</ref>.</p>
        <p>If you meet Dr. <persName>
Reiss</persName>
          <note n="4" place="foot" type="editorial">

            <persName>

Johann Wilhelm Reiss (1838-1908)</persName>, deutscher Forschungsreisender und Vulkanologe; keine Korrespondenz in HSA.</note> please give him my kindest regards. I would like to have his address in order to send him some publications relating to <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
Brazil</hi>,</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1383">Orville A. Derby</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
        <postscript>
          <pb facs="#IMG.3" n="3"/>
          <p>[<note n="5" place="foot"
                type="editorial">Auf der letzten freien Seite von Schuchardts Hand mehrere Namen, von denen er vermutlich Post erhalten oder an die er selber geschrieben hatte. Im HSA ist davon lediglich eine Korrespondenz mit em Letztgenannten <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2102">Conto de Magalhães</persName> - HSA 
06773 vom 29. 1. 1882 - nachgewiesen.</note> 21 Dec 81. Dr. J. B. de Almeida Nogueira 20 Mai 82. H. Lämmert 26. Dec. 82. Gabriele de <note
              n="6" place="foot"
              type="editorial">Dieser Teil ist unleserlich.</note> –– 83 ? (Schreiner) 10 Mai 82. <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2102">Conto de Magalhães</persName>]</p>
        </postscript>
      </div>
